         <div type="apparatus">
           <listApp>
            <app loc="ii"><note>is now (since <date>2002</date>) in a far better position than before.</note></app>
            <app loc="ii 3"><note>For <foreign xml:lang="grc">ΕΝΟ</foreign> in <bibl><ptr target="roueche1989"/>
                  <title level="m" type="abbreviated">ALA</title>
               </bibl> I now read <foreign xml:lang="grc">ΕΜΟ</foreign>; at the end of the line the letter might be <foreign xml:lang="grc">Π</foreign>.</note></app>
           </listApp>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" source="#ala2004">
            <ab>i. If it was permitted, Balerianos, who was the leader of your troop, would have wished to make even a golden image of your virtue - indeed <supplied reason="subaudible">I swear</supplied> by yourself. Doulkitios, because you were an unbroken tower of lawfulness. But now he has set you in marble in front of the baths, so that the stone may remain as a witness of your labours.</ab>
            <ab>ii. Place of <seg cert="low">chief <rs type="profession" key="thermopolos">hot-food-seller</rs>
               </seg>.</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>i. see discussion at <ref type="eAla-text" n="IV.24" target=".xml"/>; ii. see discussion at <ref type="eAla-text" n="XI.11" target=".xml"/>
            </p>
            <p>For Doulkitios, see also <ref type="inscription" n="38" target="iAph040202"/>.ii and iii.</p>
         </div>
